ommand Control Settings\\n\\nThe `commandAllowlist` array contains commands treated as safe and run without additional confirmation, regardless of autonomy prompts, and should include only low-risk utilities you rely on frequently (for example ls, pwd, dir).\\n\\nThe `commandDenylist` array contains commands that always require confirmation and are typically blocked because they are destructive or unsafe (for example recursive rm, mkfs, or privileged system operations).\\n\\nCommands that appear in both lists default to the denylist behavior, and any command that is in neither list falls back to the autonomy level you selected for the session.\\n\\n### Autonomy Levels\\n\\nThe autonomy levels include Specification Mode (droid will research and create a plan without making changes), Normal (allows reading files and executing low-risk, read-only commands), Medium (enables file modifications and medium-risk commands that are easily reversible), and High (allows all commands but still maintains safety through allow/deny lists).\\n\\n### Configuration File\\n\\nThe settings are stored in `~/.factory/settings.json`, which contains CLI settings and allow/deny lists.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"d62c0301-d547-4ea3-9725-98fbdaf5ff91\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T14:39:01.362Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"query\":\"site:docs.factory.ai droid interactive permissions autonomy settings.json\",\"results\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"srvtoolu_01DtEo4Pd9HTvpSvZXY8tmRG\",\"content\":[{\"title\":\"Factory Documentation - Settings: Configure Droid\",\"url\":\"https://docs.factory.ai/cli/configuration/settings\"},{\"title\":\"CLI Reference - Factory Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.factory.ai/reference/cli-reference\"},{\"title\":\"Droid Exec (Headless) - Factory Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://docs.factory.ai/cli/droid-exec/overview\"},{\"title\":\"Video Walkthrough - Factory Documentation\",\"url